About This Dashboard
This dashboard tracks Corewell Health's performance in the U.S. News & World Report (USNWR) Best Hospitals evaluation for Adult Specialties and Procedures & Conditions (P&C). It brings together specialty rankings, P&C ratings, and the underlying measure-level results for Corewell campuses (Grand Rapids, Troy, Royal Oak), with peer hospital comparisons to contextualize performance.
What's Included
Adult Specialties — USNWR evaluates hospitals across 15 adult specialties. Twelve are scored on a 0–100 scale using data-driven domains (outcomes, patient experience, care-related indicators such as nurse staffing, and expert opinion), while three (Ophthalmology, Psychiatry, Rehabilitation) are ranked on physician reputation alone. Hospitals ranking in the top 50 nationally are recognized as "ranked"; others may earn "high performing" designations.
Procedures & Conditions — USNWR rates hospitals as High Performing, Average, or Below Average in ~20 common procedures and conditions (e.g., heart failure, COPD, hip replacement). These ratings are based primarily on risk-adjusted outcomes (mortality, readmissions, home discharge), patient experience, and volume, drawn largely from Medicare claims.
Data Sources & Methodology
Measure-level results reflect USNWR's published methodology, developed with RTI International. Underlying data sources include Medicare claims (MedPAR), HCAHPS patient experience surveys, the AHA Annual Survey, and the Doximity physician survey. Measure definitions, weights, and risk-adjustment approaches change year over year; cross-year comparisons in this dashboard are aligned to a curated measure catalog with unique measure IDs to maintain consistency where methodology allows. Where USNWR has redefined or retired a measure, trends are flagged or broken accordingly.
How to Use
Use the campus and specialty/P&C selectors to drill from overall rankings down to individual measure results. Peer cohort views compare Corewell campuses against similar hospitals to distinguish true performance gaps from case-mix or structural differences.
Caveats
Rankings reflect data with a multi-year lag (Medicare claims typically trail 2–3 years). Results shown here are analytic replications and enrichments of published USNWR data and may differ slightly from official publications. This dashboard is for internal quality improvement use only.
